OL,3,CDriver who killed 'good Samaritan'
OL,4,Cguilty of murder
OL,6,FProsecutor Jason Pitter KC told the
OL,7,Fjury at the opening of the trial that
OL,8,FJhangur was guilty of murder because
OL,9,Fhe intended "at the very least to
OL,10,Fcause really serious harm" when he
OL,11,Fused his car as a weapon.
OL,13,FHe said that Jhangur's target may have
OL,14,Fbeen the Khan family, but the law
OL,15,Fstated "intentions can be transferred
OL,16,Ffrom one person to another, even if he
OL,17,Fdid not intend to hit that particular
OL,18,Fperson".
